2 SENATE BILL 577
1 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
2 INDICATED.
3 (B) “AMMUNITION” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 5–133.1 OF THIS TITLE.
4 (C) “FIREARM” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 5–101 OF THIS TITLE.
5 5–902.
6 (A) (1) THE MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH SHALL:
7 (I) PREPARE LITERATURE RELATING TO FIREARMS AND
8 AMMUNITION THAT INCLUDES INFORMATION REGARDING:
9 1. FIREARM SAFETY;
10 2. FIREARM TRAINING;
11 3. SUICIDE PREVENTION;
12 4. MENTAL HEALTH AWARENESS; AND
13 5. CONFLICT RESOLUTION; AND
14 (II) DISTRIBUTE THE LITERATURE TO ALL COUNTY HEALTH
15 DEPARTMENTS IN THE STATE.
16 (2) EACH COUNTY HEALTH DEPARTMENT SHALL DISTRIBUTE THE
17 LITERATURE RECEIVED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION TO ALL
18 ESTABLISHMENTS THAT SELL FIREARMS OR AMMUNITION WITHIN THE COUNTY.
19 (B) AN ESTABLISHMENT THAT RECEIVES LITERATURE UNDER SUBSECTION
20 (A)(2) OF THIS SECTION SHALL:
21 (1) MAKE THE LITERATURE VISIBLE AND AVAILABLE AT THE POINT
22 OF SALE FOR ANY FIREARM OR AMMUNITION PURCHASE; AND
23 (2) DISTRIBUTE THE LITERATURE TO EACH PERSON WHO PURCHASES
24 A FIREARM OR AMMUNITION.
25 (C) (1) EACH COUNTY HEALTH DEPARTMENT SHALL AUTHORIZE A
26 REPRESENTATIVE OF THE COUNTY’S HEALTH DEPARTMENT WHO MAY ISSUE A

SENATE BILL 577 3
1 CITATION TO AN OWNER OF AN ESTABLISHMENT WITHIN THE COUNTY’S
2 JURISDICTION THAT VIOLATES THIS SECTION.
3 (2) (I) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS SUBJECT TO:
4 1. FOR A FIRST VIOLATION, A CIVIL PENALTY NOT
5 EXCEEDING $500; AND
6 2. FOR A SECOND OR SUBSEQUENT VIOLATION, A CIVIL
7 PENALTY NOT EXCEEDING $1,000.
8 (II) A CIVIL PENALTY IMPOSED UNDER THIS PARAGRAPH SHALL
9 BE PAID TO THE COUNTY THAT ISSUED THE CITATION UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF
10 THIS SUBSECTION.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
12 October 1, 2025.

